Reasoning: The paper discusses the universality result for Consensus in distributed computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the importance of having distinct IDs, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also touches upon information theory (cs.IT) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) in its analysis of the relationship between Naming and Consensus.
